Foul Bay is a large and beautiful bay, beach and local community on the South East Coast of Barbados. It is one of the more unspoiled beaches on the Island, named its lack of suitability as a harbour in the 16th, 17th and 18th centuries. It is a suitable place to moor and store small boats.
